> Avoid doing field initialization outside constructor. (ConstructorShouldDoInitialization)

It should, instead, not complain but ignore the static field initialization outside the constructor.

A main constructor is the one that does the real work by setting all the necessary fields in the class, all other constructors should just delegate work to it.

Qulice should complain in such case:

```
public class Car {
    private final Engine engine;
    private final Steering steering;

